E. C. SOLINSKY v. UNITED STATES. No. 7859. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 17, 1935. George Neuner, of Portland, Or., for appellant. Carl C. Donaugh, U. S. Atty., of Portland, Or.

Before WILBUR, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; judgment of dismissal filed and entered accordingly, and mandate forthwith.
